3. Task Class
Purpose:
The Task class represents an individual task in the to-do list. Each task has its own properties and behaviors that define its state and characteristics.

Actions and Activities:

Store Properties: Maintains properties like description, dueDate, and status.
Update Properties: Allows for changing the details of the task, such as updating the description or changing the due date.
Status Management: Can include methods to mark the task as complete, pending, or in progress, depending on the application's needs.
